title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1625-3.5 - Approval of resolutions passed by authority
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1625-3.5 - Approval of resolutions passed by authority

State Regulations

Resolutions, passed by an authority, which require the
approval of the division will be the subject of separate correspondence. The
normal inclusion of such resolutions in minutes of a meeting will not be deemed
a request for division approval. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9
§§
1625-3.5

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
